 9. TOOLS USED TO BUILD KNOWLEDGE GRAPHS

## 9.1 Neo4j

Neo4j is a popular graph database used for building Knowledge Graphs.

### Features

* Property graph model
* Cypher query language
* Graph visualization
* Fast relationship traversal

### Example Query


MATCH (p:Person)-[:WORKS_AT]->(c:Company)
RETURN p, c


---

## 9.2 Protégé

Protégé is an ontology editor developed by Stanford University.

### Features

* Ontology design
* OWL support
* RDF support
* Semantic modeling

### Uses

* Ontology creation
* Semantic web applications

---

## 9.3 Apache Jena

Apache Jena is a Java framework for semantic web applications.

### Features

* RDF storage
* SPARQL support
* Ontology management

### Advantages

* Open source
* Semantic reasoning support

---

## 9.4 RDF4J

RDF4J is a framework for processing RDF data.

### Features

* RDF database
* SPARQL queries
* Semantic data processing

---

## 9.5 GraphDB

GraphDB is a semantic graph database.

### Features

* RDF storage
* Semantic reasoning
* Enterprise scalability

---

## 9.6 Stardog

Stardog is an enterprise Knowledge Graph platform.

### Features

* AI-powered graph analytics
* Data virtualization
* Reasoning engine

---

## 9.7 Amazon Neptune

Amazon Neptune is a cloud-based graph database service.

### Features

* RDF and property graph support
* High scalability
* Cloud integration

---

## 9.8 ArangoDB

ArangoDB is a multi-model database supporting graph structures.

### Features

* Graph database support
* Query optimization
* Flexible data storage

